articles.author: Eduardo Baptista, Hyunsu Yim, Joyce Lee
articles.description: Authorities were en route on Friday to execute an arrest warrant for impeached South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol, Yonhap News Agency reported, as a crowd of protesters faced off with police outside his residence and vowed to block any attempt.
articles.title: South Korea authorities moving to arrest impeached President Yoon, Yonhap says

articles.author: Hyunsu Yim, Eduardo Baptista, Minwoo Park
articles.description: Supporters of impeached South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol are adopting "Stop the Steal" slogans popularised by U.S. President-elect Donald Trump supporters and said they hoped the incoming president would help their embattled leader.
articles.title: Supporters of South Korea's Yoon adopt 'Stop the Steal', hope Trump will help

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel carried out air strikes on dozens of Hamas targets in Gaza over the past 24 hours, it said on Friday, in attacks that Palestinian health authorities said had killed nearly 100 people.
articles.title: Israeli air strikes ramp up Gaza death toll amid new truce push

articles.author: Marek Strzelecki, Lili Bayer
articles.description: Poland launched its presidency of the Council of the European Union on Friday mired in a diplomatic row with Hungary that underscored a deepening sense of political disunity across Europe just as it confronts a raft of major global challenges.
articles.title: Spats, divisions mar start of Poland's EU presidency

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The foreign ministers of Germany and France said they wanted to forge a new relationship with Syria and urged a peaceful transition as they visited Damascus meet its de facto new leader Ahmed al-Sharaa on behalf of the European Union.
articles.title: German, French foreign ministers in Damascus to meet Syria's new rulers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The smallest of the three centrist parties in Austria's coalition talks, the liberal Neos, is quitting the talks, the Neos's leader said on Friday, throwing into disarray the negotiations that have excluded the far-right Freedom Party.
articles.title: Austrian liberals quit coalition talks, throw process in turmoil

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Finnish court on Friday denied a request for the release of an oil tanker suspected by police of damaging an undersea power line and four telecommunications cables last week.
articles.title: Finland court rejects request for release of tanker in undersea cables probe

articles.author: Erin Banco, Jonathan Landay
articles.description: U.S. law enforcement and intelligence agencies are concerned about copycat vehicle-ramming attacks following the New Year's Day attack in New Orleans by a U.S. Army veteran, according to a U.S. law enforcement intelligence bulletin published on Friday.
articles.title: U.S. law enforcement worried about copycat vehicle-ramming attacks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Palestinian man and his son were killed in Jenin, in the Israeli-occupied West Bank, local medical officials said on Friday, as a month-long standoff between Palestinian security forces and armed militant groups in the town continued.
articles.title: Three Palestinians killed in standoff with security forces in West Bank

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Iran's foreign ministry summoned the Italian ambassador on Friday over the detention of an Iranian national wanted by the United States for his alleged role in a deadly drone strike against U.S. forces, Iranian state media reported.
articles.title: Iran summons Italian ambassador over arrest of Iranian wanted by US
